 of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Old Norse personal name <i>Sumarlíðr</i>, probably originally a byname meaning ‘summer traveller’. This is a Highland name, borne by the founder of the powerful and widespread Clan Macdonald, Lords of the Isles from the 12th to the 15th century, and it is still occasionally bestowed on members of Clan Macdonald and its septs."],"variants":[{"name":"Summerlad","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Somerled  , being taken by folk etymology as derived from the words <i>summer</i> and <i>lad</i>."]}]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"the","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Dorothea  , also used independently."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Somerled of the Isles King Of Man\"the Viking\" was born about 1125, in Morven, Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom. He married Ragnhild or Rachel or affrica of isle of Man Princess. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died on 1 January 1164, in Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 40, and was buried in Kintyre, Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1125–1 January 1164":"umbes 1125–1. jaanuar 1164","1127–Female":"1127–Surnud","1130–1198":"1130–1198","1159–1210":"1159–1210","1125–1164":"1125–1164","1127":"1127","1159":"1159","1125":"1125","1210":"1210","1198":"1198","1164":"1164","1130":"1130","Abt 1159":"umbes 1159","Abt 1125":"umbes 1125","1 January 1164":"1. jaanuar 1164","Of, Morven, Argyleshire, Scotland":"Morven, Argyll, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Abbey Of Saddell, Kintyre, Argule, Scotland":"Kintyre, Argyll, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Ixworth, Suffolk, England":"Ixworth, Suffolk, Englan